I think it may be convenient to consider with this Amendment the Amendment in the name of the right hon. Member for Blackpool, North (Sir T. Low), in page 2, line 16, at end to insert: Provided that for the year 1961–62 and each subsequent year the amount of the general grant payable to any recipient authority shall not be such that by reason of it a loss, ascertained in the manner set out in section fifteen of this Act, accrues to any rating authority. and also the Amendment in the name of the hon. and learned Member for Kettering (Mr. Mitchison), in page 2, line 16, at end to insert:
(3) (a) The prescribed aggregate amount of general grants shall not for any one year be less and may be more than the minimum stated in this subsection;
(b) the said minimum shall be the total of the existing grants or as the case may be, the prescribed aggregate amount of general grants, in either case for a preceding year (hereinafter called "the standard year"), increased if in the year to which the minimum applies the sum of the estimated population of England, Wales and the Isles of Scilly and of the estimated number of children in that population under fifteen years of age exceeds the corresponding sum in the standard year, by an increase bearing the same proportion to ten times the said total or aggregate amount as the said excess bears to the said corresponding sum;
(c)the standard year shall he the year next but one before the year to which the minimum applies.
The right hon. Member for Blackpool, North can have a Division on his Amendment in due course, if he wishes.
